listitem.para:
Once you get some output, you can increase &kdump; verbosity. Setting
  KDUMP_VERBOSE to 11 turns on debugging output during all stages of the &kdump;
   process and results in the following behavior:

If kdump initramfs does not generate correctly, turn on debugging when generating it;
mkdumprd -fd. You can also unpack and inspect the generated initramfs image with the lsinitrd --unpack /var/lib/kdump/initrd
 command.
